From bc7341c8f7f47e36188131367fc1b80757d45300 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ben Browning <bbrownin@redhat.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 00:16:18 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] [Frontend] Fix tool calls leaking as content when no
 reasoning precedes them
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

In agentic flows the model may output <|tool_call> immediately after a
tool response with no reasoning block. DelegatingParser stayed in
reasoning phase because (CONTENT, TOOL_START) transitions lacked
REASONING_END, so it never switched to the tool adapter.

Fix by adding REASONING_END to (CONTENT, TOOL_START) transitions in
both Gemma4 and Qwen3 configs — matching (REASONING, TOOL_START) which
already declares it. The existing skip_tool_parsing handler in
_on_terminal now covers this path with no engine-layer special case.

Add tool-after-tool-response scenario to the trace builder and plumb
prompt_token_ids through the replay harness so the scenario is tested
across all chunk sizes, holdback depths, and DelegatingParser replay.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

Signed-off-by: Ben Browning <bbrownin@redhat.com>
